ARC Render Cluster - Master Control Program

1-Introduction
	The ARC MCP is a program designed to monitor the physical status off the 
	machines in a compute cluster.  It's mission is to streamline many of the
	arduous tasks of cluster management, and monitor the cluster collecting
	useful metrics along the way.
